11. Shared Responsibilities

All frontend developers are expected to:

Follow the approved design system.
Build reusable and responsive React components.
Use TypeScript and Tailwind CSS consistently.
Integrate mock data from JSON.
Follow Git workflow using feature branches and pull requests.
Participate in code reviews.
Write clean, maintainable, and documented code.
Ensure accessibility and responsive design.
12. Non-Functional Requirements

The application must be:

Fully responsive (Desktop, Tablet, Mobile)
Fast and optimized
Accessible (basic WCAG compliance)
Consistent in design
Easy to maintain
Built with reusable components
Support Light and Dark Mode
13. Expected Deliverables

By the end of the internship, the team should deliver:

A fully responsive frontend MVP
15+ application pages
30+ reusable UI components
Interactive dashboards and charts
Mock AI chat experience
Complete navigation flow
Organized GitHub repository with clear commit history
Project documentation, including setup instructions and component usage
14. Success Criteria

The project will be considered successful if:

All assigned modules are completed and integrated.
Navigation between all pages works seamlessly.
Mock data accurately powers the dashboard and analytics.
The AI Advisor provides realistic, mock business insights.
The UI is polished, responsive, and consistent across devices.
The codebase is modular, reusable, and ready for future backend integration.
